28/04/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A mass grave containing the bodies of three members of Romanian's anti-communist resistance group, White Guard, turned up on Monday (April 27th) near the village of Nepos in northern Romania, media reported. The grave contained bones and a boot that will undergo forensic analysis, said experts from the Romanian Institute for the Investigation of Communist Crimes. Authorities tentatively identified the dead as Ioan Leonida Bodiu, Ioan Burdet and Toader Dumitru. The communist-era secret police Securitate executed and buried them in 1949. (Mediafax, Ziare, Focus - 27/04/09) 
